    "content": "{\"id\":\"0io4zp\",\"version\":1,\"rows\":[{\"id\":\"y9xtl2\",\"cells\":[{\"id\":\"yf636g\",\"size\":6,\"plugin\":{\"id\":\"asiinema-player/plugin\",\"version\":1},\"dataI18n\":{\"default\":{\"url\":\"https://asciinema.org/a/448073.cast\"}},\"rows\":[],\"inline\":null},{\"id\":\"lkanrx\",\"size\":6,\"plugin\":{\"id\":\"ory/editor/core/content/slate\",\"version\":1},\"dataI18n\":{\"default\":{\"slate\":[{\"type\":\"HEADINGS/HEADING-ONE\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"How it works\"}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"asciinema project is built of several complementary pieces:\"}]},{\"type\":\"LISTS/UNORDERED-LIST\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"LISTS/LIST-ITEM\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"command-line based terminal session recorder, \"},{\"text\":\"asciinema\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\",\"}]},{\"type\":\"LISTS/LIST-ITEM\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"website with an API at asciinema.org,\"}]},{\"type\":\"LISTS/LIST-ITEM\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"javascript player\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"When you run \"},{\"text\":\"asciinema rec\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\" in your terminal the recording starts, capturing all output that is being printed to your terminal while you’re issuing the shell commands. When the recording finishes (by hitting Ctrl-D or typing \"},{\"text\":\"exit\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\") then the captured output is uploaded to asciinema.org website and prepared for playback on the web.\"}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Here’s a brief overview of how these parts work.\"}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"\"}]}]}},\"rows\":[],\"inline\":null}]},{\"id\":\"9c62xr\",\"cells\":[{\"id\":\"t7su39\",\"size\":12,\"plugin\":{\"id\":\"ory/editor/core/content/slate\",\"version\":1},\"dataI18n\":{\"default\":{\"slate\":[{\"type\":\"HEADINGS/HEADING-TWO\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Recording\"}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"You probably know \"},{\"text\":\"ssh\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\", \"},{\"text\":\"screen\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\" or \"},{\"text\":\"script\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\" command. Actually, asciinema was inspired by \"},{\"text\":\"script\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\" (and \"},{\"text\":\"scriptreplay\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\") commands. What you may not know is they all use the same UNIX system capability: \"},{\"type\":\"LINK/LINK\",\"data\":{\"href\":\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudo_terminal\",\"openInNewWindow\":false},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"a pseudo-terminal\"}]},{\"text\":\".\"}]},{\"type\":\"BLOCKQUOTE/BLOCKQUOTE\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"A pseudo terminal is a pair of pseudo-devices, one of which, the slave, emulates a real text terminal device, the other of which, the master, provides the means by which a terminal emulator process controls the slave.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Here’s how terminal emulator interfaces with a user and a shell:\"}]},{\"type\":\"BLOCKQUOTE/BLOCKQUOTE\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"The role of the terminal emulator process is to interact with the user; to feed text input to the master pseudo-device for use by the shell (which is connected to the slave pseudo-device) and to read text output from the master pseudo-device and show it to the user.\"}]}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"In other words, pseudo-terminals give programs the ability to act as a middlemen between the user, the display and the shell. It allows for transparent capture of user input (keyboard) and terminal output (display). \"},{\"text\":\"screen\",\"CODE/CODE\":true},{\"text\":\" command utilizes it for capturing special keyboard shortcuts like Ctrl-A and altering the output in order to display window numbers/names and other messages.\"}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"asciinema recorder does its job by utilizing pseudo-terminal for capturing all the output that goes to a terminal and saving it in memory (together with timing information). The captured output includes all the text and invisible escape/control sequences in a raw, unaltered form. When the recording session finishes it uploads the output (in \"},{\"type\":\"LINK/LINK\",\"data\":{\"href\":\"https://github.com/asciinema/asciinema/blob/master/doc/asciicast-v1.md\",\"openInNewWindow\":false},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"asciicast format\"}]},{\"text\":\") to asciinema.org. That’s all about “recording” part.\"}]},{\"type\":\"PARAGRAPH/PARAGRAPH\",\"data\":{\"align\":\"left\"},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"For the implementation details check out \"},{\"type\":\"LINK/LINK\",\"data\":{\"href\":\"https://github.com/asciinema/asciinema\",\"openInNewWindow\":false},\"children\":[{\"text\":\"recorder source code\"}]},{\"text\":\".\"}]}]}},\"rows\":[],\"inline\":null}]}]}"
